docs.text: if you haven't plunked down your hard-earned money yet for " wild wild west , " the latest summer holiday offering from will smith , let me say right now that your money will be better spent on a starbuck's frappacino or on a ben & jerry's sundae .

docs.text: these treats are great relief from the summer heat .

docs.text: in contrast , this film made me simmer in disappointment .

docs.text: i can accept the fact that summer movies tend to put more weight into special effects and that good stories and flavorful characters usually take a back seat .

docs.text: this was true of star wars episode i , but at least in that film , the story and the characters were still in the back seat .

docs.text: in this film , they are no where to be found .

docs.text: what remains are hundreds of male extras costumed as gunslingers and foppish aristocrats , lots of female extras who look like can-can dancers , and a clunky , 80-foot tall instrument of destruction that resembles a mechanical tarantula .
